{"id":"7982","name":"Reddit Image To Wallpaper","tagline":"Grabs the 2nd best post that is an image, can add text, and makes it your wallpaper.","icon":"ios14 c463140863 g61440","latest":"24250","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This script selects the highest rated post from a subreddit that is an image, unless the top post is an image. Then it gets the second highest rated post. This is so that you always know there is something in that subreddit that is worth seeing. You can provide your own favorite subreddit in the script.</p>\n<p>It then optionally adds text to the image, and posts it as your wall paper, scaled to show the full width of the image, but allow for the parallax effect (motion). It adds a blurred background complimenting the image to any areas not covered.</p>\n<p>This script requires 2 additional shortcuts to be installed:\nWallpaper - Overlay Image On Blurred Version Of Itself: https://routinehub.co/shortcut/7978/</p>\n<p>Overlay Text On A Photo: https://routinehub.co/shortcut/7981/</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>0.7 - Jan. 3, 2021, 1:03 a.m.</strong></p>"}